@incollection{Haser.2006,
 abstract = {Adverbs easily constitute the most heterogeneous of all word classes; they often are described as a `dustbin' category to which items will be assigned that do not fit into other word classes. Semantically and morphologically, adverbs are most closely related to adjectives, from which they are often derived.

