@incollection{Song.2006,
 abstract = {The causative construction is a linguistic expression that denotes a complex situation consisting of two events: (1) the causing event in which the causer does something, and (2) the caused event in which the causee carries out an action or undergoes a change of condition or state as a result of the causer's action. The following example is such a linguistic expression.

