The fact that Papuan Malay has /giawas/ with -/w/- is an almost certain indication that it derives from Malay, not from Spanish.~ The initial stops of loanwords are highly irregular and variable, as seen in Spanish /papaya/, /papaya-s/, but Pangasinan /apayas/, Tagalog /papaya/, Bikol /tapayas/, Western Bukidnon Manobo /kepayas/, Yakan /kapaya/ ~'papaya'.~ What is distinctive (and indicative of probable historical connection) here, is the -w-, not the g-~in /giawas/.},
